<p>
<seg id=1> The Nicaraguan ambassador to America, Sacasa, called on creditor nations to reduce the debt of central American countries and provide these countries with larger sums of aid in order to help the them the recover from the damage caused by hurricane Mitch. </seg>
<seg id=2> Sacasa said on American television that about US$1 billion would be needed to rebuild Nicaragua, and he asked America and other creditor nations to make an integrated economic aid plan similar to the Marshal Plan to rebuild Western Europe after World War II. </seg>
